I"Ê<p>In this tutorial we will learn about file operators in Shell Programming by using the <a href="/bash/conditions">if statement</a> to perform tests</p>

<p>Operator 	Note
-e 	To check if the file exists.
-r 	To check if the file is readable.
-w 	To check if the file is writable.
-x 	To check if the file is executable.
-s 	To check if the file size is greater than 0.
-d 	To check if the file is a directory.</p>

